The paper discusses the use of Prolog-based ECLiPSe system for solving algorithmic problems from the Google Code Jam programming contest using declarative techniques like constraint logic programming and linear (integer) programming. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category, as it focuses on the use of a specific programming language and its features for solving problems. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques like constraint logic programming, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with data structures and algorithms, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of linear programming could also suggest that the paper belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of declarative programming compared to imperative programming, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, as machine learning often involves optimizing algorithms for efficiency.
